         <abstract>
            <p> The <foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt</foreign> by <persName ref="PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</persName> is a version of 
               the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1961Mashaf">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt</ref>, a Church service made up of psalms, biblical readings and hymns. 
               It eventually replaced  <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2230Saatat"/>.</p>
            <p>The three other types of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt</foreign> identified by  <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Taft1986Liturgy"/>
                  <citedRange unit="page">266</citedRange>
               </bibl> are: </p>
            <p> 
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2230Saatat"/>: the Coptic Saʿātāt;</p>
            <p> a <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3576Saatat">Saʿātāt that includes the entire Psalter</title> in the daily pensum, cp. ;</p>
            <p>
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3576Saatat"/>: a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</foreign> that includes the entire Psalter in the daily pensum;</p>
            <p>
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3577GizeS"/>: a cursus of prayers which is not really a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</foreign>, but a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Gize ṣalot</foreign> for hermits and recluses.</p>
         </abstract>
